commentBody:
Speaking as someone who is not vegan, this was *delicious.* I made small changes to method to speed things up and improve texture:

1. Soaked the cashews in boiling water for about 20mins;
2. Steamed the sweet potato whole in the microwave (wrapped in a damp paper towel), 3 mins. at a time, until very soft;
3. Microwaved the tofu for about 2 mins. to help release moisture, draining the excess liquid;
4. Blended the cashews in our electric spice/coffee grinder to make sure they were perfectly smooth, adding maple syrup slowly until fully incorporated.

We did not have maple extract, but didn’t miss it. As others have mentioned, the crust is very salty. I might reduce the salt slightly next time, but it does make a nice contrast with the sweet filling. 

We will definitely make this again when we are hosting guests with dietary restrictions.

@Daryl
“advanced enough to use the metric system” HAHAHA!
True.
